1. Overview & Architecture
This runbook covers all prerequisite steps and configuration actions required to enable virtual machine replication from a VMware vCenter source environment to a Nutanix NC2 (Nutanix Cloud Clusters) target environment. The primary replication tool used is Nutanix Move — a purpose-built, agentless/agent-assisted VM migration appliance.

1.1 Replication Tool: Nutanix Move
Nutanix Move (formerly Xtract for VMs) is a free migration appliance provided by Nutanix. It is deployed as a virtual appliance (OVA/OVF) on the source vCenter environment and orchestrates:
•	Discovery of VMs from vCenter
•	Snapshot-based disk replication to Nutanix AHV (NC2)
•	Incremental (delta) sync cycles to minimize cutover downtime
•	Driver injection and NIC conversion for AHV compatibility
•	Optional agent-based replication for improved performance and reduced RPO

1.2 High-Level Architecture
The replication flow is as follows:

①	VMware vCenter + ESXi Hosts  (Source VMs)	→	Nutanix Move Appliance  (Replication Engine)	→	Nutanix NC2 / AHV  (Target)

1.3 Replication Modes
Mode	Description	Use Case
Agentless	Move connects via vCenter APIs, uses VMware CBT (Changed Block Tracking) for incremental sync. No agent installed on source VMs.	General migrations; VMs where agent installation is not permitted
Agent-Based	Move Agent installed on source VM guest OS. Provides better performance, reduced RPO, and supports VMs not visible via vCenter.	Preferred mode for production VMs; supports physical-to-virtual (P2V)

 
