11. Troubleshooting — Replication Phase

Issue	Likely Cause	Resolution
Move appliance cannot reach vCenter	Firewall blocking TCP 443	Open TCP 443; verify Move appliance IP is in allow-list on vCenter firewall
VM stuck at 0% seed copy	TCP 902 blocked / CBT not enabled	Open TCP 902 from Move to ESXi; enable CBT on source VM; restart replication
Move agent shows 'Disconnected'	TCP 8088 blocked or agent service down	Check guest OS firewall; verify move-agent service is running; check Move appliance IP config
Pre-flight check fails: 'Snapshot failed'	Insufficient datastore space for snapshot	Free up space on source datastore; reduce number of concurrent replications
Delta sync shows high lag / RPO exceeded	Insufficient bandwidth or high VM change rate	Enable bandwidth throttle; reduce concurrent VMs; schedule delta syncs during off-peak
Test cutover VM has no network (on NC2)	Network mapping incorrect in Move plan	Review and correct network mappings in the migration plan; re-run test cutover
Test cutover VM fails to boot / BSOD (Windows)	VirtIO drivers missing / boot config	Install Nutanix VirtIO drivers on source VM before replication; re-seed replication
Authentication error on NC2 target	Prism credentials changed / expired	Update Prism service account credentials in Move target environment settings

📞  Escalation:  For unresolved Move issues, raise a support case via Nutanix Portal (portal.nutanix.com) and provide the Move support bundle: Move UI → Settings → Collect Logs.

